# qyl

**Question Your Logs** — Compile-Time AI Observability OS

## What qyl Is

A platform where every tool, schema, span, metric, and agent surface is generated at compile time from annotated C# classes. Zero runtime reflection. Full AOT. OTel-correct. Claude-native.

|                 |                                                                                    |
|-----------------|------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| **Collects**    | OTLP receiver (gRPC 4317 / HTTP 5100) with idempotent upsert, DuckDB 1.5.0       |
| **Generates**   | Roslyn source generators emit MCP tools, JSON schemas, OTel spans, JSON contexts   |
| **Queries**     | 77+ MCP tools with compile-time dispatch, structured output, and Server Card       |
| **Instruments** | GenAI + DB interceptors via `[Traced]`/`[OTel]`/`[Meter]`/`[AgentTraced]`          |
| **Automates**   | Loom agent: triage, RCA, fix generation, code review — all observable via OTel     |
| **Visualizes**  | React 19 dashboard with SSE streaming, ECharts 6, TanStack Table                  |
| **Publishes**   | Server Card (`.well-known`), `mcp.json`, `llms.txt`, structured SKILL.md           |

## Tech Stack

| Layer      | Technology                                              |
|------------|---------------------------------------------------------|
| Runtime    | .NET 10.0, C# 14, `PublishAot=true`                     |
| Frontend   | React 19, Vite 7, Tailwind CSS 4, Base UI 1.3.0         |
| Storage    | DuckDB 1.5.0 (Debian, single-writer, ON CONFLICT upsert)|
| Protocol   | OTel SDK 1.15.0, Semconv 1.40, MCP Semconv 2026         |
| Schema     | TypeSpec -> OpenAPI -> C# / DuckDB / TypeScript          |
| MCP        | ModelContextProtocol C# SDK 1.2.0, Streamable HTTP       |
| Generators | Qyl.Agents (unified), qyl.instrumentation.generators, qyl.collector.storage.generators |
| Build      | NUKE 10.1.0, MSBuild, ANcpLua.NET.Sdk                    |
| Auth       | OAuth 2.1 + DCR, DPoP (RFC 9449), Workload Identity Federation |
| Agent      | Microsoft Agent Framework (MAF) — `AsAIAgent()` pattern   |

## The Generator

One Roslyn source generator (`Qyl.Agents.Generator`) powers the entire MCP tool surface. You write:

```csharp
[McpServer("qyl")]
partial class QylObservabilityServer(CollectorClient client)
{
    [Tool(ReadOnly = true)]
    [Description("Search traces by service, operation, status, or time range. Returns trace IDs, durations, and error counts. Use when investigating latency or failures across services.")]
    async Task<string> SearchTraces(
        [Description("Service name filter (exact match)")] string? service = null,
        [Description("Minimum duration in milliseconds")] int? minDurationMs = null,
        [Description("Maximum results (1-100, default 25)")] int limit = 25,
        CancellationToken ct = default)
    {
        // your code — everything else is generated
    }
}
```

The generator emits:

| Output | What | AOT |
|--------|------|-----|
| `CreateMcpTools(IServiceProvider)` | `McpServerTool[]` factory — plugs directly into official SDK's `WithTools()` | Yes |
| `DispatchTool_{Name}Async(JsonElement, CancellationToken)` | Per-tool dispatch with direct `JsonElement.GetProperty` accessors | Yes |
| `s_schema_{Name}` | Static `byte[]` JSON Schema per tool — zero runtime cost | Yes |
| `{ClassName}JsonContext` | `[JsonSourceGenerationOptions]` partial class for complex return types | Yes |
| `ActivitySource("Qyl.Agents")` | Per-tool OTel spans following MCP semconv 2026 | Yes |
| `Histogram<double>("mcp.server.operation.duration")` | Transport-level + tool-level duration metrics | Yes |
| `GetServerCard()` | `.well-known/mcp-server` Server Card document | Yes |
| `GetSkillMarkdown()` | SKILL.md content for Claude Code plugin distribution | Yes |
| `GetLlmsTxt()` | `llms.txt` for LLM-facing discovery | Yes |

Skill assignment is an attribute: `[QylSkill(QylSkillKind.Inspect)]` on the server class. The generator knows everything. No hand-maintained rosters.

### Compile-Time Diagnostics

| ID | Severity | What |
|----|----------|------|
| QA0001 | Error | `[McpServer]` class must be partial |
| QA0005 | Error | Duplicate tool name |
| QA0008 | Warning | Parameter missing `[Description]` |
| QA0011 | Warning | Tool description fewer than 50 characters (Claude quality) |
| QA0012 | Warning | Parameter description fewer than 10 characters (Claude quality) |
| QA0013 | Info | Consider `input_examples` for complex schemas |

Bad tool descriptions get caught at build time, not after deployment.

## OTel: MCP Semantic Conventions 2026

Every tool call produces a two-level span hierarchy:

```text
HTTP SERVER span (auto, Kestrel)
  +-- MCP SERVER span: "tools/call search_traces"
  |     mcp.method.name = "tools/call"
  |     gen_ai.tool.name = "search_traces"
  |     mcp.protocol.version = "2025-06-18"
  |     mcp.session.id = "sess_abc"
  |     jsonrpc.request.id = "42"
  |     jsonrpc.protocol.version = "2.0"
  |
  +---- INTERNAL span: "execute_tool search_traces"
          gen_ai.operation.name = "execute_tool"
          gen_ai.tool.name = "search_traces"
          gen_ai.tool.type = "function"
          gen_ai.tool.call.id = "call_xyz"
```

Metrics: `mcp.server.operation.duration` (transport) + `gen_ai.client.operation.duration` (tool execution). Both generated. Both collected by qyl.collector.

## MCP Transport

| Client | stdio | Streamable HTTP |
|--------|-------|-----------------|
| Claude Code | Yes | Yes |
| Claude Desktop | Yes (local) | Yes (Connectors) |
| Claude Web UI | -- | Yes (required) |
| Messages API (MCP Connector) | -- | Yes (required) |
| Cursor, Windsurf | Yes | Yes |

One binary, two transports. `QYL_MCP_TRANSPORT=http` for remote, stdio by default for local.

### Server Card

```text
GET /.well-known/mcp-server
```

Returns a machine-readable document describing the server's capabilities, tool count, transport, auth requirements, and version. Generated at compile time from the `[McpServer]` attribute.

### Structured Output

Tools can declare output schemas. Claude validates its response against the schema before returning:

```csharp
[Tool(OutputSchemaType = typeof(TraceSearchResult))]
async Task<TraceSearchResult> SearchTraces(...) { ... }
```

The generator emits the output JSON Schema alongside the input schema. Claude sees both.

### Tasks (Long-Running Operations)

```csharp
[Tool(TaskSupport = TaskSupport.Required)]
async Task<string> RunRootCauseAnalysis(string traceId, CancellationToken ct) { ... }
```

The generated dispatch wraps the tool in `ExecuteToolAsTaskAsync` — Claude gets a task ID immediately, polls for status, and fetches the result when ready. Retry semantics and expiry policies per MCP 2026 Tasks primitive.

## Auth

| Mode | When |
|------|------|
| None | Local stdio, development |
| Bearer token | `QYL_MCP_TOKEN` for simple deployments |
| JWT (Keycloak) | `QYL_KEYCLOAK_AUTHORITY` for enterprise SSO |
| OAuth 2.1 + DCR | Claude Web UI, API connectors, remote MCP |
| DPoP (RFC 9449) | Token-bound access for zero-trust environments |
| Workload Identity | Cloud-native: platform-issued JWTs, no shared secrets |

