## Architecture

```text
                    +------------------------------------------+
                    |      Official MCP C# SDK (v1.2.0)        |
                    |  Streamable HTTP + stdio + OAuth 2.1     |
                    +-------------------+----------------------+
                                        | hosts
                    +-------------------v----------------------+
                    |        Qyl.Agents.Generator               |
                    |  Compile-time: dispatch, schemas, OTel,   |
                    |  JSON contexts, Server Card, SKILL.md     |
                    +-------------------+----------------------+
                                        | generates
    +-------------------+-------------------+-------------------+
    |                   |                   |                   |
    v                   v                   v                   v
+--------+      +--------+      +----------+      +-----------+
|qyl.mcp |      |qyl.loom|      |qyl.collec|      |   qyl     |
|77 tools |      |3 tools |      |tor API   |      | dashboard |
|Streamable      |triage  |      |DuckDB    |      | React SPA |
|HTTP+stdio      |RCA/fix |      |OTLP ingest      | SSE stream|
+--------+      +--------+      +----------+      +-----------+
    |                |                 ^                  ^
    +----------------+-----------------+                  |
                     | HTTP only                          |
                     +------------------------------------+
                     qyl.collector owns storage (single-writer)
```

## Triggers and Events (MCP 2026)

Servers can proactively notify clients when data is available:

```csharp
[Trigger("error.new")]
[Description("Fires when a new error issue is created")]
async Task OnNewError(ErrorIssue issue, IMcpNotificationSink sink, CancellationToken ct)
{
    await sink.NotifyAsync($"New error: {issue.Title} in {issue.Service}");
}
```

qyl.collector detects new error patterns -> fires trigger -> Claude receives notification -> initiates triage without being asked.

## Quick Start

```bash
# Collector
docker run -d -p 5100:5100 -p 4317:4317 -v ~/.qyl:/data ghcr.io/ancplua/qyl:latest

# MCP (local)
QYL_COLLECTOR_URL=http://localhost:5100 qyl.mcp

# MCP (remote, for Claude Web UI)
QYL_MCP_TRANSPORT=http QYL_COLLECTOR_URL=http://localhost:5100 qyl.mcp

# Dashboard
cd src/qyl.dashboard && npm run dev

# Point any OTel app at qyl
export OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT="http://localhost:5100"
```

## Instrument Your .NET App

```csharp
builder.AddQylServiceDefaults();
```

Auto-instruments `IChatClient` (Microsoft.Extensions.AI) with OTel 1.40 GenAI semantic conventions. Token usage, latency, model info, finish reasons — all captured, all queryable via MCP tools.

## TypeSpec-First Design

```text
core/specs/*.tsp -> core/openapi/openapi.yaml -> C# / DuckDB / TS / JSON Schema
```

Single source of truth. Never edit generated files.

